<a class="definition-word" data-category="general-biology" id="toxin">Toxin</a> - A substance (small <a href="#molecule">molecule</a>, peptide, <a href="#protein">protein</a>) that kills cells or even whole organisms. Toxin-antitoxin pairs can be useful in biotechnology where the presence of the antitoxin confers resistance to the toxin, enabling <a href="#selection">selection</a>. Producing a toxin as the output of a circuit can be used in medical applications, <em>exempli gratia</em> to kill cancerous cells or infectious <a href="#bacteria">bacteria</a>.